column10:
project zomboid is what i would call a hardcore, realistic open world survival horror that does not forgive. zomboid is a hard but fair game at its core. this game has realistic survival mechanics that you have to keep stable or else risk debuffs or death. zomboids building mechanics are realistic but are fun to mess around with whether it be building your very own base on your own or secure and protect a already existing house, the system is very giving to both play styles. the class and perk system for zomboid is a very customizable but fair system that anyone can use to build there own perfect character with its own downside to make things balanced that can be perfected in game through hard work and practice to completely get rid of or maintain these debuffs. whether it be a super weak and slim burglar that can hot-wire cars, or a medic that's super buff but as a base intellect of a carrot, the game is highly adaptive to fight any play style and even change certain styles in game through the stat system. zomboid is one of the hardest but most fun zombie survival games I've ever played. the game is very adaptive with different events that happen as the in game time moves forward, like winter, nature retaking buildings and even houses being raided by other survivor as the time goes on (there are no npc survivors in game as of now). personally i haven't made it past the first week but every time i die or lose a character, i learn what went wrong and how to deal with or evade certain scenarios. that's why this game is so great because rng isn't  the cause for most deaths, there all caused by you. this game is still only in an open beta but there are so many different features and updates that im excited to see as the game evolves and becomes more streamlined to newer players.

TLDR;
this is a zombie horror game that has great character trait systems with excellent crafting and building systems that is punishing but fair.
